text: Really love the fish soup here - the fish pieces are sizeable and portion is quite generous. Each of them are fresh, tender yet still full of bite. Soup is deliciously made with lots of garlic (although it can get salty sometimes), tofu, tomatoes and veggie. It's a comfort food for sure and something I think of getting regularly. Recommended to try for sure! Service is not the best though but don't let that put you off from the delicious bowl of fish soup!

Be forwarded that Jing Fish soup stall owner make it mandatory for customers to divulge their personal contact number when payment with paynow. In addition, he will take a snap shot of your phone bank transfer. If you refuses to reveal your contact number, he will withhold the food from you even your digital payment has successfully processed and transferred to them.

No more $3.50 fish porridge. The fish soup stall suddenly changed the budget meal to fried fish head which is totally inedible. So many fish bones and no meat, not suitable for old people. I won’t come to this coffeeshop anymore, time to boycott

$6.50 for fish porridge and fish soup and there’s only 4 slices of fish. The fish soup also tastes very salty and unhealthy to consume. Worst fish soup stall I have eaten. Thought it’s a healthy option but it turns out to be a scam
The fish soup porridge is good, served piping hot. Open till 1159pm for those looking at healthier options during late hours.
